{"word":"ἀλγεινός","slug":"ἀλγεινός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀλγεινός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἄλγος'><el>ἄλγος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b>attic for epic <el>ἀλεγεινός</el>, <i>giving pain, painful, grievous</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-νῶς</el>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>rare in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> sense, <i>feeling pain, grievously suffering, suffering</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b> —<a href='S:confer, compare'>Cf.</a> <el>ἀλγίων, -ιστος.</el><p/></div>"}]}